South Africa’s trade surplus widened in November as the value of imports of equipment components and chemical products decreased. The R6.1 billion positive balance compares with a revised R2.75 billion surplus in October, the Pretoria-based South African Revenue Service said Friday in a statement on its website. The median estimate of four economists in a Bloomberg survey was for a surplus of R12.2 billion. Key insights © 2019 Bloomberg L.P.